          <msContents>
            <summary>Collections of Gāyatrī mantras meant for use in supplementary post-Vedic rituals. Text evokes the Advaita Vedānta philosopher Śaṃkarācārya at the end (f. 2v), suggesting the texts intended retroactive correlation with that tradition.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Mahāvākyagāyatrīcathurthapāda</title>
              <title type="vernacular">महावाक्यगायत्रीचथुर्थपाद</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śaṃkarācāryaḥ // iti māhāvākyagāyatrīcaturthapādasamāptaḥ śrīsītārāmacadrārpaṇam astu // śubhaṃ bhavatu // (f. 2v).</colophon>
